items.name: Phantom Corsair (1938)
items.description:
The Phantom Corsair, also known as the "Flying Wombat," is an iconic concept car that was designed in the 1930s. It was the brainchild of Rust Heinz, the heir to the H. J. Heinz Company fortune, and Maurice Schwartz, an experienced automobile designer.

The Phantom Corsair was intended to be a futuristic luxury automobile with a sleek and aerodynamic design. It featured a low-slung body made of hand-formed aluminum, which gave it a distinctive and streamlined appearance. The car had unique design elements such as hidden wheels, recessed door handles, and an absence of running boards.

Inside, the Phantom Corsair had a luxurious and spacious cabin that could accommodate up to six passengers. It boasted innovative features for its time, including a push-button transmission, power windows, and a built-in radio system. The car was also equipped with advanced engineering, such as a Cord 812 drivetrain, which provided it with impressive performance capabilities.

Despite its innovative design and advanced features, the Phantom Corsair never went into mass production. Only one prototype was ever built, which still exists today and is considered a rare and valuable collector's item. The car made appearances in various films and has gained a cult following over the years due to its unique and futuristic aesthetic.

The Phantom Corsair stands as a testament to the visionary design of the 1930s and continues to be admired as an iconic and influential concept car.

items.name: Confused girls at computers [CONCEPT]
items.description:
Have you ever thought "Man I really need a LoRA to make confused girls sitting at computers"? No? Just me then?

I made this as an experiment to see if it was possible to make a good concept LoRA on just one image and the answer is "no". So I retrained with a second image made by the LoRA itself and the answer became - eh, kinda, fun to play with for a bit so I figured I'd share it.

The art style is very strict but it seems to work OK with character LoRAs. Slightly more reliable using DPM++ 2M Karras, at least on AOM2. Recommended LoRA strength 0.8 to 1.0. Note that the dataset had square images so using other aspect ratios might break things or add more panes.


If anyone wants to use this LoRA to make more images to train on for a better version feel free, no rights reserved whatsoever.


Original image created by the artist naavs.

A request of @alextravis8888729.

D√©bora Gomes is a social media personality from Portugal, with more than 1M followers on Tiktok.

130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (d3borag0mes:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

items.name: Inflatable Dolls

I had to cook this one a lot to get transparent breasts working, so you may need to turn the weight down and parameters up if you want to preserve your model's look. Consequently, it also tends to preserve faces since half the data set had that look. items.name: John Martin Style
items.description:
John Martin was an English painter and printmaker known for his dramatic and monumental landscapes.

His style can be described as Romantic, characterized by vast, apocalyptic scenes and a sense of awe-inspiring grandeur.

Martin's paintings often depicted cataclysmic events such as floods, storms, and volcanic eruptions, evoking a sense of both awe and terror.

He had a unique ability to capture the sublime power of nature, with swirling clouds, towering cliffs, and cascading waterfalls dominating his compositions.

Martin's use of light and shadow added to the dramatic effect of his works, heightening the emotional impact on the viewer.

His art found great popularity during the 19th century, appealing to the public's fascination with the sublime and the exploration of the unknown.

Today, John Martin's artworks continue to captivate audiences with their epic scale and evocative portrayal of nature's elemental forces.

Also make sure to prompt the eyes, otherwise they will look weird.

Note: This was made exclusively on anime images and on an anime checkpoint. Feel free to post images on realistic, semirealistic etc. checkpoints, but do not rate it on that! This was made to be used on anime checkpoints so keep reviews for that!

His style can be described as highly detailed and realistic, showcasing his exceptional skill in capturing the likeness and character of his subjects.

Copley's portraits often depicted prominent figures of his time, including political leaders, wealthy merchants, and historical figures.

He had a meticulous approach to composition, utilizing rich colors, elaborate costumes, and intricate backgrounds to enhance the visual impact of his paintings.

Copley's works demonstrated a balance between naturalistic representation and a touch of elegance, reflecting both his artistic talent and the societal aspirations of his patrons.

His contributions to American art during the 18th century laid the foundation for future generations and established him as one of the leading portrait painters of his era.

Karisma Kapoor is a Bollywood heartthrob from the 90s and early 2000s. Coming from a long line of actors, she was the only actress at the time that could pull of traditional Indian clothing and short skirts with equal aplomb.

Lycos are quirky. This one's quirk is that it needs the 'restore faces' to be turned off. Also used very few negative prompts (see sample images) - otherwise effect of the Lyco quickly reduces.

It is also tending to produce images that look more anime like, but the end results look good, so am uploading. May follow up with a version that looks more photorealistic.

Suggested settings:

  1. Sampler: Euler a, DDIM for first pass, then img2img for upscaling with DPM++ 2M SDE Karras

  2. Steps: 20-30

  3. CFG scale: 6-7.5

  4. Strength: 1-1.25

items.name: Cyber Background
items.description:
Introducing Cyber Background Model: An AI Model for Generating Cyberpunk backgrounds.

Cyber Background Model is specifically designed to generate captivating and immersive backgrounds inspired by the cyberpunk genre and neon-lit environments. Trained on a dataset comprising images of cyberpunk cityscapes and neon places, the model has undergone 20 epochs and 1760 steps to master the intricacies and visual characteristics of these futuristic and vibrant settings.

The dataset used to train Cyber Background Model was carefully curated to include a wide range of cyberpunk and neon-inspired images. These images showcase the iconic elements of cyberpunk aesthetics, such as towering futuristic skyscrapers, neon-lit streets, holographic billboards, and bustling cityscapes. By training on this dataset, the model has gained a deep understanding of the visual elements that define cyberpunk and neon environments.
